
Unit 1 AM/IS/ARE

1.2) Writer am, is or are.

1) The weather (is) nice today.
2) I (am) not rich.
3) this bag (is) heavy.
5) Look! there (is) Helen.
4) these bags (are) heavy.
6) My brother and I (are) good tennis players.
7) Emily (is) at home. her children (are) at school.
8) I (am) a taxi driver. My sister (is) a nurse.


1.3) Complete the sentences.

1) steve's ill. he's in bed.
2) i'm not hungry. but (i'm) thristy.
3) mr thomas' a very old man.  he('s) 98.
4) these chairs aren't beautiful, but they're comfortable.
5) the weather's nice today. (it's) warm an sunny
6) you're late. not i'm not late. i'm early. 
7) catherine isn't at home. she's at work.


8) (here's) your coat. oh thank you very much.

