2.2 Make questions with these words.


1. (is / at home / your mother):  is your mother at home?
2. (your parents / are / well):  are you parents well?
3. (interesting / is / your job): is your job interesting?
4. (the shops / are / open today): are the shops open today?
5. (from / where / you / are): where are you from?
6. (interested in sport / you / are): are you interested in sport?
7. (is / near here / the station): is the satition neat here?
8. (at school / are / your children): are you children at school?
9. (you / are / late / why): why are you late?

2.3 Complete the questions. Use W h at... / Who ... / Where ... / How .

1. (how are) your parents? they're very well.
2. (where's) the bus stop? at the and of street.
3. (how old are) your children? five, six and ten.
4. (how much are) these oranges? $1.5 a kilo.
5. (what's) your favourite sport? skiing.
6. (who) the man in this photo? that' my father.
7. (what colour are) your new shoes? back.

